# Shared Package Rules

## Purpose

The shared package contains types, schemas, and utilities used by BOTH frontend and backend.

## Structure

```
packages/shared/src/
├── types/      # TypeScript interfaces
├── schemas/    # Zod validation schemas
├── utils/      # Shared utilities
└── index.ts    # Export all
```

## Type Rules

### All entities must be defined in shared/types/

```typescript
export interface User {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  email: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}

export interface Group {
  id: string;
  name: string;
  memberIds: string[];
  createdBy: string;
  createdAt: Date;
  updatedAt: Date;
}
```

### DTOs must be defined

```typescript
export interface CreateGroupDto {
  name: string;
  description?: string;
  memberIds: string[];
}
```

## Usage

### Frontend

```typescript
import { Group, CreateGroupDto } from '@cost-share/shared';
```

### Backend

```typescript
import { Group, CreateGroupDto } from '@cost-share/shared';
```

## Rules

- NO "any" types
- All types must be exported
- Use strict TypeScript
- Document complex types
- Keep types simple and focused
